	<div class="posts">
	<a name="108829489484384994"></a>
    
    <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-08-31 -->
    
    Linking the Atom Feeds
    
    </font></h2>
    
    
    <p>
	<div style="clear:both;"></div><strong>Missing Atom Links.</strong>&nbsp; The template that we began with, <a href="http://www.blogger.com/templates/rounders3/sample.html">Rounders 3</a>, does not display any Atom Links.&nbsp; The Atom syndication feed is activated, but there is no way to find it.&nbsp; The feed button and a text link are now operating.&nbsp; This was accomplished as follows:<ol><li>A procedure for linking to an Atom feed was outlined and carried out, with screen shots, and turned into a provisional document, <a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/B040603.htm">Atom Feed Me, Feed Me</a>.</li><li>The procedure was carried out in the <a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/wingnut/2004/06/linking-atom-feed.asp">Muddleware Lab</a>, with the procedure adjusted as we went.</li><li>After verifying that the procedure worked properly, I first changed the template here to <a href="http://www.blogger.com/templates/rounders2/sample.html">Rounders 2</a>, just for variety, and then made the same changes for addition of Atom feed links.</li></ol>The Atom feeds are now operating on both of these laboratory sites, and new posts carry links that make it easy to find them for syndication.<div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
    </p>
	<span class="byline">posted by orcmid
       at <a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless/2004/06/linking-atom-feeds.asp">6/26/2004 05:24:00 PM</a>,
       rating 
       <script src="http://www.newsgator.com/ngs/ratings.aspx?rurl=http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless/2004/06/linking-atom-feeds.asp">
       </script> data by <a href="http://www.newsgator.com">NewsGator 
